<br>
I saw these somewhere too, and a very interesting point was made:<br>
<br>
Currently, the exp received from certain encounters is very very minimal, so simply sharing current exp would result in such LITTLE exp as to be not worth the coding problems.<br>
<br>
So, I think they actually stated a potential &quot;fix&quot; for this would be to increase the exp given for such encounters, with the assumption that exp would be shared.<br>
<br>
When you get into this situation, you'd have to be very careful to not make this exploitable, wherein a mob currently giving, say, 1,000,000 points of exp total now gives 50,000,000 points and someone finds a way to focus all that exp on one person or one group.<br>
<br>
I don't know how they'd know WHEN to add exp and to whom, but they are thinking about the possibility.<br>
