<br>
The issue with raiding and xp that I see is fairly simple. Raids are not about XP. However, seeing that yellow message tends to give you a warm fuzzy feeling - Hey my group rocks! This is cool!<br>
<br>
Its rather depressing being in the non-xp group and NEVER seeing that yellow message even once. You work your butt off but it makes no difference - you can't directly see that you are benefitting the raid. Youre slowing, buffing, healing isn't this as important as dealing massive damage?<br>
